HEADWORD: Harassment
<hw>Har"ass*ment</hw> <pr>(-m⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act
of harassing, or state of being harassed; worry; annoyance;
anxiety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Little <qex>harassments</qex> which I am led to suspect do
occasionally molest the most fortunate.</q> <rj><qau>Ld.
Lytton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harberous</ent>⟦br⟧
